:collection_of_collagen_fibrils rdfs:subClassOf :acellular_anatomical_structure .
text: collection of collagen fibrils is a type of acellular anatomical structure.

Bone collagen fibril is the same as the intersection of a collection of collagen fibrils and something that is at least part of some bone element. It is a type of collection of collagen fibrils and also a type of something that is at least part of some bone element. Additionally, a bone collagen fibril is defined as the connective tissue bundles in the extracellular matrix of bone tissue that are composed of collagen, and they play a role in tissue strength and elasticity.

The anterior uvea is a multi-faceted structure within the eye that serves various functions and has a complex nature. As a type, it falls under the category of caro 0000000, multi tissue structures, ectoderm-derived structures, and is considered part of the uvea. More specifically, the anterior uvea includes parts such as the iris and the ciliary body. It is defined as the front (ventral) portion of the vascular, pigmentary, or middle coat of the eye, which encompasses both the ciliary body and the iris. In terms of nomenclature, the anterior uvea is also known by several exact synonyms, including Haller tunica vascula, anterior part of uveal tract, anterior uveal tract, anterior vascular layer of the eyeball, anterior vascular tunic of the eye, tunica vasculosa bulbosa, and ventral uveal tract. Additionally, it has related synonyms like ciliary body and iris, and vasculosa oculi, indicating its close association with these components and functions within the eye.
Ingested food, defined as a substance that is consumed by the organism for food, is a type of organism substance.

Head or neck skin is defined as a zone of skin that is part of a craniocervical region, which means it is the same as something that is both a zone of skin and at least part of some craniocervical region. This establishes that head or neck skin is a type of zone of skin and also a type of something that is at least part of some craniocervical region.

Columnar epithelium is a type of epithelium that is defined as an epithelium consisting of columnar epithelial cells. These cells are characterized by their height, which is at least four times their width. Furthermore, columnar epithelia can be divided into two categories: simple (or unilayered) and the rarer stratified (or multi-layered).

Meso epithelium is identified as a type of epithelium and also as a type of mesoderm-derived structure. It is precisely defined as epithelium that derives from the mesoderm, aligning with its characterization as the same as the intersection of epithelium and something that at least develops from some mesoderm. Additionally, meso epithelium is exactly synonymous with mesoderm-derived epithelium and mesoepithelium.

The embryonic facial prominence is a type of embryonic structure and is part of the head. It is defined as one of five swellings formed during the development of the face. This structure is also known by other names including embryonic facial process, facial primordium, and primordium of face.

The bone of the jaw is the same as something that intersects with a bone element and something that is at least a part of some jaw region. It is classified as a type of facial bone, a type of digestive system element, and a type of something that is at least part of some jaw skeleton. The bone of the jaw is defined as a bone element that is part of a jaw region and has the exact synonym "jaw bone."
The internal anal region is a type of multi-tissue structure that is at least partially part of some anal region.

The cloacal vent is the same as an orifice that intersects with at least part of some cloaca. It is defined as the opening of the cloacal chamber to the outside of the organism, such as in birds which maintain a single cloacal opening throughout their lives. Additionally, the cloacal vent is referred to by exact synonyms including "cloacal opening" and related synonyms "cloacal orifice" and "vent."

The extraembryonic cavity is the same as something that intersects with an anatomical space and something that is at least a part of the entire extraembryonic component. It is a type of anatomical space as well as a type of entity that is at least part of some entire extraembryonic component. Additionally, the extraembryonic cavity is synonymously related to extraembryonic cavities.

The skeleton of the pectoral complex is a type of subdivision of the skeleton and is part of the appendicular skeleton and the pectoral complex. It is defined as the collection of all skeletal elements in a pectoral complex, which includes the combination of a free limb or fin plus the pectoral girdle. The skeleton of the pectoral complex is also related to several synonyms, including bones of the upper limb, ossa membri superioris, pectoral complex skeleton, set of bones of the upper limb, skeleton of anterior limb/fin and girdle, and the upper limb skeleton.

Cloacal mucosa is the same as something that intersects with something that is mucosa and something that is at least part of some cloaca. It is a type of mucosa, and also a type of something that is at least part of some cloaca. The definition of cloacal mucosa is "A mucosa that is part of a cloaca," which is automatically generated. Furthermore, cloacal mucosa has several exact synonyms, including cloaca mucosa, cloaca mucosa of organ, cloaca mucous membrane, cloaca organ mucosa, cloacal mucous membrane, mucosa of cloaca, mucosa of organ of cloaca, mucous membrane of cloaca, and organ mucosa of cloaca.

The cloacal epithelium is the same as something that is an intersection of something that is epithelium and something that is at least part of some cloaca. It is a type of digestive tract epithelium, a type of endo epithelium, and also a type of something that is at least part of some cloaca. The definition of cloacal epithelium is an epithelium that is part of a cloaca. Additionally, the cloacal epithelium has a related synonym, which is the cloacal endoderm.

A future brain vesicle is categorized as an open anatomical space, and it is part of at least some ventricular system of the central nervous system as well as part of some future brain. It is exactly synonymous with both early brain vesicle and primitive brain vesicle. Furthermore, future brain vesicle is narrowly synonymous with primary brain vesicle and secondary brain vesicle. It also has a related synonym, brain vesicle.

A subdivision of a tube is categorized as a type of organ part and is also identified as belonging to something that constitutes at least a part of some tube. Additionally, it is recognized as a type of entity that must include some part of an anatomical wall and some part of an anatomical space.

The foramen of the skull is defined as an anatomical space that is an opening in a bone of the skull, which is the same as the intersection of a bone foramen and something that is at least part of some skull. This makes the foramen of the skull a type of bone foramen as well as a type of entity that is at least part of some skull. In terms of terminology, "foramen of the skull" is an exact synonym for itself, while it has narrow synonyms including "cranial conduit" and "cranial foramen." Additionally, it has a related synonym, "foramina of the skull."

An anatomical conduit space is a type of anatomical space, and it is also a type of something that is at least part of some anatomical conduit. Furthermore, it is characterized as a type of something that connects exactly two anatomical spaces. The anatomical conduit space is defined as an anatomical space which is the lumen of some anatomical conduit and connects two or more spaces together, as modified from the FMA. Additionally, it has a narrow synonym known as foramen space.

The main body axis is a type of organism subdivision and is defined as a principal subdivision of an organism that includes all structures along the primary axis, typically the anterior-posterior axis, from head to tail. This includes structures of the body proper where present, such as ribs, but excludes appendages.

The body proper is categorized as a type of organism subdivision and is considered a part of the main body axis. It is defined as the region of the organism associated with the visceral organs. Related synonyms for the body proper include "body" and "whole body."

An integumentary projection is defined as an anatomical projection that is part of the integumental system and is the same as something that intersects both an anatomical projection and at least part of some integumental system. It is a type of anatomical projection as well as a type of integumentary adnexa. Moreover, an integumentary projection has a narrow synonym: skin projection.

The integumentary system layer is defined as an organ component layer that is part of an integumental system, which means it shares the same properties as the intersection of organ component layers and entities that are at least part of some integumental system. It is classified as a type of organ component layer and also as a type that is at least a part of some integumental system. Furthermore, the integumentary system layer is narrowly synonymous with "layer of skin" and "skin layer."

A digestive system element is the same as something that is both an organ and at least a part of some digestive system. It is categorized as a type of organ and also as a type of entity that is at least part of some digestive system. The definition of a digestive system element encompasses any of the organs or elements that are part of the digestive system, with examples including the tongue, esophagus, spleen, crop, lunge feeding organ, and tooth elements. Additionally, "digestive organ" and "digestive system organ" are exact synonyms for a digestive system element.

The future telencephalon is a type of presumptive structure and also a type of entity that constitutes at least part of some future forebrain. It is defined as an embryonic structure that gives rise to the telencephalon. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with the presumptive telencephalon.

Mesenchyme derived from the neural crest is defined as mesenchyme that develops from the neural crest, which is automatically generated. It is a type of mesenchyme and also considered a type of neural crest-derived structure. This concept is exactly synonymous with mesenchyme from the neural crest, neural crest derived mesenchyme, and neural crest mesenchyme. Furthermore, it is identical to the intersection of something that is mesenchyme and something that at least develops from some neural crest.

The thoracic skeleton is a subdivision of the skeleton, categorized as part of the thoracic segment of the trunk and the postcranial axial skeleton. It is defined as the subdivision of the skeletal system comprising all skeletal elements in the thoracic region of the trunk, which, in most vertebrates, includes the rib cage and sternum. Furthermore, the thoracic skeleton is exactly synonymous with the skeleton of the thorax, the thoracic part of the axial skeleton, and the thoracic skeleton itself.

The anal membrane ectodermal component is characterized by being a subtype of unilaminar epithelium, ecto epithelium, and is a part of the anal region. This component is identical to an intersection that encompasses unilaminar epithelium, entities that are at least partly part of the anal region, and entities that at least develop from the ectoderm. Additionally, it is defined as a unilaminar epithelium that develops from the ectoderm and is part of the anal region.

Prosomere is equivalent to something that is both a neuromere and at least part of some future forebrain. It is defined as a neuromere that is part of the presumptive forebrain. Additionally, prosomere is identified as a type of neuromere and also as a type of entity that is at least part of some future forebrain. In terms of terminology, prosomere is broadly synonymous with both forebrain segment and segment of forebrain, and it has an exact synonym, which is forebrain neuromere. Moreover, it is relatedly synonymous with future prosencephalon.

The cloacal muscle is a type of muscle organ that is also considered a part of the digestive system element. It is defined as any muscle organ that is part of a cloaca. Furthermore, it is equivalent to the intersection of a muscle organ and something that is at least part of some cloaca, illustrating its significant relationship with the cloaca.

The musculature of the pectoral complex shares the same characteristics as something that intersects with the musculature and something that is at least a part of some pectoral complex. It is classified as a type of musculature and also as a type of something that is at least a part of some pectoral complex. The definition of the musculature of the pectoral complex is any collection of muscles that is part of a pectoral complex, where the pectoral complex includes the pectoral girdle and the associated limb or fin. Furthermore, the musculature of the pectoral complex has several narrow synonyms, including muscles of the upper limb, musculature of the upper limb, musculi membri superioris, set of muscles of the upper limb, and upper limb musculature.

Primordial vasculature is a type of primordium and something that constitutes at least part of the embryonic cardiovascular system. It is defined as a portion of tissue that will develop into vasculature.
A non-connected functional system is a type of disconnected anatomical group, defined as an anatomical group whose component structures share a common function.

A lateral structure is a type of anatomical structure and also falls under the category of something that is at least part of some material anatomical entity. It is defined as any structure that is placed on one side of the left-right axis of a bilaterian.

A circulatory organ is classified as a type of compound organ and is also considered a part of the circulatory system to some extent. It is defined as a hollow, muscular organ that, by contracting rhythmically, aids in the circulation of lymph, blood, or analogs; examples include a chambered vertebrate heart, the tubular peristaltic heart of ascidians, the dorsal vessel of an insect, and the lymph heart of a reptile. When it comes to terminology, "heart" is recognized as a broad synonym for a circulatory organ, while "cardiac pump" and "heart or heart-like organ" are considered its exact synonyms. Additionally, "circulatory vessel" is a narrow synonym, and "cardiac structure" is a related synonym.

The respiratory system basement membrane is identified as a specific type of basement membrane that is part of the respiratory system's connective tissue. It shares the same characteristics as the intersection of the basement membrane of epithelium and any component that is at least a part of the respiratory system. In essence, this basement membrane is defined as a basement membrane of epithelium that is integral to the respiratory system.

The combination of the heart and pericardium is recognized as an element of the thoracic cavity and is also considered a part of the cardiovascular system, at least to some extent. Additionally, this combination is exactly synonymous with the term "heart/pericardium."

Axilla skin is identical to something that is an intersection of a zone of skin and something that is at least a part of an axilla. It is also defined as a type of skin located in the clavicle region and as a type that is at least part of an axilla. Moreover, the axilla skin is defined as a zone of skin that is part of an axilla. Additionally, axilla skin has exact synonyms, including axillary skin and skin of the axilla.

The smooth muscle layer in the fatty layer of subcutaneous tissue is identified as a specific type of smooth muscle tissue that intersects with a portion of the hypodermis. It is defined as a smooth muscle tissue that forms part of the hypodermis. Furthermore, this smooth muscle layer is known by exact synonyms, including "muscle layer in fatty layer of subcutaneous tissue" and "stratum musculosum panniculi adiposi telae subcutaneae."

The eye epithelium shares the same characteristics as the intersection of an epithelium and an entity that is at least part of some camera type eye. It is identified as a type of pigment epithelium of the eye, a type of ecto epithelium, and a type that is at least part of some camera type eye. Furthermore, the eye epithelium is defined as an epithelium that is part of a camera-type eye.

The foregut epithelium is defined as an epithelium that is part of a foregut. It is identical to the intersection of epithelium and entities that are at least partially part of the foregut. Furthermore, the foregut epithelium is categorized as a type of digestive tract epithelium and also as a type of entity that is at least partially part of some foregut.

The future central nervous system is categorized as a type of presumptive structure, which constitutes at least a part of some future nervous system and is something that at least develops from some ectoderm. It is defined as the primordium that develops into the central nervous system. Furthermore, it is exactly synonymous with both "future CNS" and "presumptive central nervous system."

The future nervous system is categorized as a type of presumptive structure and is defined as the primordium that develops into the nervous system. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with the term "presumptive nervous system."

The entire extraembryonic component is a type of multi-tissue structure and is considered to be a part of some conceptus. It is defined as the part of the conceptus that may be lost before birth, will be discarded at birth, or when the embryo becomes an independent organism. Moreover, it has exact synonyms, including extra-embryonic component and extraembryonic component.

A transitional anatomical structure is a type of developing anatomical structure. It is defined as an embryonic anatomical entity that will transform into one or more other anatomical entities, perhaps alongside other anatomical entities, later in development.

A developing mesenchymal structure is a subtype of developing anatomical structure, as well as a subtype of something that at least partially consists of mesenchyme. Furthermore, it is defined as a mesenchyme-derived anatomical entity that is undergoing a transition to become another structure.
